## Facade-risk investigation (CLAUDE.md §3.4)

`__R2_FORCE_PLAN_THROW` env var is read ONLY inside the `vi.mock` factory in `event_round2_invariants.test.ts:313`. NOT read in any production code. The mock is created at module-load time inside the test file — fully test-only, impossible to ship.

## Round-2 contract tests are not tautological

- Provenance test: pins both compile-time (BaseInputs shape) and runtime (every make* returns provenance:'test' under VITEST regardless of dry_run hint).
- FACTORY_RUN_ID test: invokes orchestrator, inspects `process.env` after — covers BOTH unset-before→deletion and set-before→restoration branches plus the early-return failure path.
- Dry-run plan test: reads actual JSONL via `readEvents`, asserts `outcome === 'ok'`.
- Exception test: triggers real exception via vi.mock, asserts `pipeline.failed` written to JSONL AND `pipeline.finished` is absent.

## Strongest parts (independent assessment)

- Provenance is genuinely unspoofable — the API surface (no `provenance` field on `BaseInputs`) plus the hardwired `VITEST > dryRun > live_run` rule makes "tests cannot lie" a TYPE-level constraint.
- Orchestrator's try/catch/finally is symmetric: every exit path (success, top-level fail, per-spec fail, exception) closes the event stream with `pipeline.finished` or `pipeline.failed` AND restores `FACTORY_RUN_ID`.

